name: From Seattle:Hiking in Mount Rainier Private Tour
description:
This trip is unique in that it encompasses the essence of Mount Rainier National Park, combining diverse natural landscapes with rich outdoor experiences. This route showcases the diverse landscapes of Mount Rainier National Park at different altitudes and perspectives, from glaciers and mountains to ancient forests and vast valleys, and each journey will bring different visual enjoyment. The chartered car service makes the entire trip more comfortable and efficient, avoiding cumbersome parking and transportation issues, allowing you to focus on enjoying the beautiful scenery without worrying about logistics, which is very suitable for family travel. The comfortable vehicle provides flexible schedules to ensure that you can fully experience each attraction, and you can also adjust the itinerary according to your interests.
Recommended attractions: Paradise area (hike Nisqually Vista Trail-hike Skyline Trail)-Grove of the Patriarchs (hike Grove of the Patriarchs Trail)-Sunrise area

name: Cozy Home near Children's Hospital & UW Medical Center at Montlake
description:
Discover Seattle serenity in our newly remodeled 2BR, 1BA retreat, 1000 sq ft of home comfort. Walkable to Seattle Children's Hospital, University Village and local gems. Longer walk or quick bike ride to UW Medical Center at Montlake and UW. Fast internet, a cozy fireplace, and washer/dryer for convenience. Unwind on the beautiful backyard patio. Your peaceful Seattle stay awaits!

Discover luxury in this newly remodeled haven featuring a spacious master bedroom with a king-sized bed and a second bedroom adorned with a queen-sized bed. The well-lit bathroom offers a spacious shower, and for added convenience, a washer and dryer are at your disposal.

Bask in the natural light streaming through the expansive windows of the living room, where a plush sofa and two swiveling/reclining chairs effortlessly transition from conversation mode to a cinematic experience. The dining room, bathed in excellent lighting, doubles as a versatile workspace. The full kitchen is a culinary haven, equipped with everything you need to prepare any meal.

Indulge in the charm of our shared backyard oasis. While it's a communal space, it offers ample room for everyone to unwind and soak in the tranquil ambiance.

Guests have complete private access to the upstairs level, the deck off the master bedroom, and the driveway for parking.

The backyard patio is a shared space.

name: Artistic Seattle's Retreat - Friends & Family Fun, Happy Hour Fun | 4 Units
description:
Our downtown location offers prime access to Seattle's icons: Pike Place Market, Space Needle, MoPOP museum. Capitol Hill delights with bars, bites, shops for night owls and foodies. Enjoy our complimentary Craft Beer happy hour and Elliott Bay views.

Nestled near downtown Seattle's Pike Place Market, our central hotel is close to the Space Needle and Museum of Pop Culture. Enjoy nearby shopping, then relax in our comfortable rooms with free Wi-Fi, craft beer hour, and yoga mats. The lobby boasts Andy Warhol art, and the service is intuitive. Stylish, pet-friendly rooms feature comfy beds. Ideal for artistic souls, creative duos, and business travelers seeking Seattle's unique culture.

PLEASE NOTE:
This listing is specifically for a hotel room located within a hotel, distinguishing it from typical residential or apartment accommodations.

- These are FOUR separate hotel rooms. Rooms are individually unique and may not be adjoining or adjacent, allocated based on availability upon arrival. The price is for all rooms. 

- The property requires a damage deposit of USD 100/night/unit on the credit/debit card provided. The deposit is required for EACH UNIT and is refunded IN FULL upon check-out.

- Early check-in is subject to availability upon arrival.

- Following property rules, the minimum age required for check-in is 21 years old;

We're delighted you're considering RoomPicks curated selection of boutique hotels, condo hotels, and resorts worldwide. This room comes with:


THE UNIT

Each 325 sqft / 30 sqm Max Room Two Doubles features:
- 2 Double Beds
- Bathtub/shower combination
- Refrigerator
- USB Bedside
- Desk
- Bluetooth Speaker
- Tea Maker
- 50 HDTV
- Daily housekeeping
All linens, towels, and bathroom essentials are provided.


THE PROPERTY

Our vibrant property provides the following on-site amenities:

- 24/7 Front desk and Security;
- Complimentary Wi-Fi
- 24-hour fitness center  
- Bicycle rentals
- Craft beer hour
- Facilities for disabled guests

name: Fox in a Box Escape Room Seattle
Seattle 90 - Minute Snapshot Tour
description: "Discover six unique Seattle neighborhoods in just 90 minutes, with photo stops along the way. From floating homes and hidden urban waterfalls to a quirky troll under a bridge, this tour packs the city's charm and character into a quick, unforgettable adventure, including Kerry Park Viewpoint. In less time than it takes to watch two episodes of "The White Lotus" you will explore one of America's most beautiful cities.

review.name: The best tour ever!!
review.reviewBody: Our driver was so entertaining and informative. We saw everything that we wanted to. Very impressed with all the sites. He also included coffee and bathroom breaks, and also accommodating to our schedule to get back on time. The best tour we ever took.

review.name: Amazing time
review.reviewBody: What an amazing tour of Seattle! Our guide Earl was absolutely incrediblefun, engaging, and incredibly knowledgeable. He didnt just stick to the script; he went above and beyond by showing us hidden spots that werent even on the agenda. We learned so much and had a great time doing it. Highly recommend!

itemListElement.name: Sky View Observatory at the Columbia Center Admission Tickets

name: Sky View Observatory at the Columbia Center Admission Tickets
description: Conveniently located in the heart of Downtown Seattle at the Columbia Center, enjoy the stunning views of the Emerald City from the tallest public viewing area in the Pacific Northwest. Your 360-degree view will include Mt. Rainier, Bellevue, the Cascade Mountains, Mt. Baker, the Space Needle and the beautiful city of Seattle!

review.name: Disappointing option
review.reviewBody: Could not go and couldnt access the itinerary to cancel it. There was no option in TripAdvisor to manage my trip to cancel or change.

review.name: Exceptional views, brilliant customer service.  Better than the  Space Needle!
review.reviewBody: This was a truly superb experience.  Our flight to Seattle was cancelled, so we missed our originally reserved slot.  The staff were FANTASTIC and allowed us to change our booking so we could visit the following day.  Everyone was so nice - the reception staff, the staff that came up with us in the lift, and the staff working in the caf / bar at the top.  The views were also breath-taking.  It was a clear day and we could see so far.  It's much higher than the Space Needle, so I'd 100% recommend booking this observation deck over the Space Needle.

review.name: what a view
review.reviewBody:
Very tall building and an amazing view from the top deck. i love the Bay View and look down to watch the traffic on the waterfront and the harbor. The city looks totally different from here. no crowd and easy access up and down.
My friend and I enjoyed a pizza and spend some time up there. absolutely no rush

review.name: Excellent observation tower!
review.reviewBody:
Excellent observation tower. Think I preferred this one to the space needle 
Lovely friendly staff made it more enjoyable

review.name: Excellent staff
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide was engaging, and the city's history is fascinating! Very well done. Lots of fun. She took us beneath and above the streets.

review.name: Nice way to see Seattle area
review.reviewBody: Queue to the lifts took around 30 minutes early morning but there are lots of information boards providing details of the tower construction, a lot which was interesting.  The 360 view at the top is worthwhile

review.name: Confusion about ticket location
review.reviewBody: I thought I purchased the space needle but it was an observation floor in another building down town so I was not able to get to that location in time for 6:15 pm slot nor was I able to get a slot at the space needle

review.name: Better than space needle
review.reviewBody: The best tour ever  so much better than the space needed and hardly any people the tour guide Darren is the best   A must do if your in Seattle

review.name: Dont miss this stop!
review.reviewBody: My husband and I, my brothers and their families recently came back from a cruise and had a few hours to kill before our flight.  We decided to take in a bus tour that included a trip to the sky view observatory.  This was truly a highlight of our time in Seattle!  Darrin Frazier was one of several working Oct. 12th but he was outstanding!  He went above and beyond to share interesting facts and his love for his job made our day spectacular.  The view didnt hurt any either the morning fog made the view from such height literally was breathtaking.  Darrin was nice enough to share many photos that he had personally taken to enhance our experience.  Thank you Darrin and Sky View Observatory for a lovely morning in Seatttle.  This is well worth the price!

review.name: Best place to view the city
review.reviewBody: The top of the highest skyscraper in Seattle for excellent views across the city.    You can even see mountains and the 2 airports in the distance.   Much better priced than space needle too.  So this is a must in Seattle

name: Seattle Scenic Tours & Wine Rides (Hourly)
description:
The chauffeur will show and allow you to pick out the top choices and go to as many sites, attractions & wineries as desired. Time can be extended if needed. There are so many beautiful sites to see.
 Dont drink n drive, get a chauffeured ride instead
